10 AS INTRODUCED
11 An Act relating to technology; prohibiting the
granting of personhood to artificial intelligence
12 systems, environmental elements, nonhuman animals,
and inanimate objects; clarifying act does not revoke
13 personhood of entities currently recognized;
providing for codification; and providing an
14 effective date.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1 of Title 75A, unless there is
20 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 A. Notwithstanding any other provisions of law, artificial
22 intelligence systems, environmental elements, nonhuman animals, and
23 inanimate objects shall not be recognized as or granted the status
24 of personhood under the Constitution or laws of this state.
HB3546 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 B. Nothing in this section shall be construed to alter or
2 revoke the status of any municipality, corporation, association,
3 partnership, nonprofit organization, or other legal entity duly
4 recognized under the laws of this state prior to November 1, 2026.
5 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
6
